-- Wigan Defeats Manchester United 1-0 in English Premier League
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-04-11T20:54:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/wigan-defeats-manchester-united-1-0-in-english-premier-league.html
Wigan defeated first-place
Manchester United 1-0 in English soccer’s Premier League, while
 Manchester City  beat West Bromwich 4-0.  Shaun Maloney scored the goal as Wigan moved out of the
three relegation places at the bottom of the 20-team standings.
The loss reduced United’s lead over second-place Manchester
City, to five points.  Sergio Aguero scored two goals and  Carlos Tevez  and David
Silva added one each as City routed West Brom to end a three-
match winless run.  Arsenal won 3-0 at Wolverhampton and Queens Park Rangers
beat Swansea 3-0 in tonight’s other games.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  